sub_title: Master Student Infection and Immunity - Utrecht University
summary: During the master's program Infection & Immunity at Utrecht University, I have gained a lot of experience. During a 9-month internship at the Kuball group in the UMC Utrecht, I focused on Immunotherapy, and worked on TEGs and their receptors. Besides, I have written a thesis about the development of therapeutics based on immune evasion molecules from pathogens. At the moment, I am doing an internship at Janssen Vaccines & Prevention B.V., where I'm focusing on the development of an ADCx bioassay, to characterize the humoral immune response against SARS-CoV-2. This is the final part of my master, meaning that it is time for the next step: a PhD position.
